# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values.

```bash
cp .env.example .env.local
```

## Supabase

Get these from your [Supabase project settings](https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api):

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key
```

## Resend (SMTP for Supabase Auth emails)

Get API key from [Resend Dashboard](https://resend.com/api-keys):

```
RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
# Optional: only set after verifying YOUR domain in Resend (see docs/EMAIL_AND_DOMAINS.md).
# Without a custom domain, leave RESEND_FROM unset and use "Copy link" for workspace invites.
# RESEND_FROM=TaskWave <hello@send.yourdomain.com>
CONTACT_INBOX_EMAIL=you@example.com
```

**No custom domain?** See [docs/EMAIL_AND_DOMAINS.md](docs/EMAIL_AND_DOMAINS.md) â€” the app works on `*.vercel.app`; automatic email requires a domain you own.

To auto-configure Supabase SMTP (optional):

```
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=sbp_...
```

Then run: `bash scripts/configure-supabase-resend-smtp.sh`

Create branded auth email templates:

```bash
bash scripts/create-resend-auth-templates.sh   # Resend templates (published)
bash scripts/sync-supabase-auth-templates.sh   # Supabase Auth HTML templates
```

Resend template aliases: `taskwave-confirm-email`, `taskwave-reset-password`, `taskwave-otp`, `taskwave-magic-link`, `taskwave-email-change`, `taskwave-invite`.

Manual SMTP in Supabase dashboard (Auth â†’ SMTP):
- Host: `smtp.resend.com` | Port: `465` | User: `resend`
- Password: your `RESEND_API_KEY`
- Sender: `TaskWave <hello@send.taskwave.app>` (after verifying `send.taskwave.app` in Resend)


Get these from [Stripe Dashboard](https://dashboard.stripe.com/test/apikeys):

```
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
STRIPE_PRICE_PRO=price_...
STRIPE_PRICE_BUSINESS=price_...
```

Create products "Pro" (â‚¬12/mo) and "Business" (â‚¬29/mo) in Stripe test mode and copy the Price IDs.

## App

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://taskwave-rust.vercel.app
PRIVACY_IP_SALT=change-me-in-production-long-random-string
NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
CONTACT_INBOX_EMAIL=hello@taskwave.app
WEBHOOK_INTERNAL_SECRET=taskwave_webhook_2026
```

For production, set `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` to `https://taskwave-rust.vercel.app` (o `https://taskwave.vercel.app` dopo averlo collegato al progetto Vercel `taskwave`).
`PRIVACY_IP_SALT` must be a long random secret â€” never reuse across environments.
